We care about the protection of your personal data. We and our partners use cookies to operate our website, to make it easier to use, and to personalize content and ads. To maintain a high level of protection of your personal data and the relevance of information about cookies and their use by our Service, the content of this policy will change from time to time.
What are cookies and what do we use them for?
"Cookies" are short pieces of data that are generated by a web server and stored on your computer, phone, tablet or other device when you visit a website.
Cookies can be used for different purposes, and our purposes are described in this policy so that you can make the choice that suits you best.
It is worth noting that cookies have a limited duration, even the so-called persistent ones. The duration of each cookie used on our website is indicated in our policy below.
What kind of cookies do we use?
We have classified our cookies based on how we use them. You can opt out of participation in all but the necessary categories, but please read this policy to the end to find out how this will affect your experience of using the website.
Please note that our Cookie Policy may include more cookies than we actually use in your country.
Change or revoke consent in our cookie policy
Your consent applies to all bookmate domains.
If you have questions and / or you need help with matters related to this Cookie Policy, you can contact us by email at
privacy@bookmate.com.
Necessary (16)
These cookies are essential for our website to function. For example, they allow you to log into your account securely. A cookie is also used to store your consent to the use of cookies. Since these cookies are essential, you cannot opt out from them.
__stripe_mid, __stripe_sid
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 1 year. Used for the operation of the payment system.
m
Set by stripe.com for a term of 2 years. Used for the operation of the payment system.
recent-views, scfc, _ga_SEKFWD1C9J, machine_identifier, docs.prefs, __stripe_orig_props, lang, private_machine_identifier
Set by stripe.com for a term of 1 year. Used for the operation of the payment system.
tmr_reqNum, tmr_lvidTS, tmr_lvid
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 1 year. Used to keep the site running.
_csrf
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 1 year. Used for security (to prevent requests for other resources from being forged using other cookies).
bms
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 1 year. Used to store the user's session.
Marketing (5)
These cookies are essential to measure marketing performance and improve the relevance of our ads and content recommendations. For example, these cookies allow us to promote new works available on the Service that we think you might like or not show you advertisements for content you are already using.
Our advertising partners and the service providers we use to deliver our email also use marketing cookies on our site to personalize the ads you see on their networks and to track the number of website hits and site accesses using advertising. We encourage you to read their privacy and cookie policy.
If you opt out from these cookies, you may still be able to see our ads on third-party websites and applications, but they will not be personalized and you may miss out on exclusive offers targeted at users of our Service.
_fbp
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 3 months. Used by Facebook to deliver a series of advertisement products such as real time bidding from third party advertisers.
sb, datr, dpr, wd
Set by facebook.com for a term of 3 months. Contains a combination of a unique browser and user ID used for targeted advertising.
Analytics (29)
These cookies are essential in order to understand how our website is used and to improve your user experience. For example, these cookies allow us to count visits and find out which pages are the most and least popular.
_ym_isad
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 20 hours. Determines whether a User is running any ad-blocking software.
_ym_visorc
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 1 year. Used to keep the site running.
_ym_uid
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 1 year. Used to identify user on the website.
_ym_d
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 1 year. Used to store the first visit to the site.
aws-client-id
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 1 year. Registers data on the behavior of site visitors. Used for internal analysis and site optimization.
af_id
Set by appsflyer.com and onelink.me for a term of 2 years. Registers data on the behavior of site visitors. Used for internal analysis and site optimization.
_ga
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 2 years. This cookie is used to recognize unique users by assigning a randomly generated number as the client ID. It is included in every page request on a site and is used to calculate visitor, session, and campaign data for site analytics reports.
_gid
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 1 day. Stores and updates a unique value for each page visited and is used to count and track page views.
client-id
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 1 year. Registers data on the behavior of site visitors. Used for internal analysis and site optimization.
ym_visorc
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 30 minutes. Registers data on the behavior of site visitors. Used for internal analysis and site optimization.
afUserId
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 2 years. Registers data on the behavior of site visitors. Used for internal analysis and site optimization.
AF_SYNC
Set by bookmate.com for a term of 7 days. Registers data on the behavior of site visitors. Used for internal analysis and site optimization.
