The best way to solve anything is sending us a letter.
Bookmate is a book club where users may bring their own content and get an opportunity to read their books using the Service. Bookmate is the platform in providing legal access to a rich collection of books and audiobooks on major mobile platforms. We work with authors and publishers to provide them with an opportunity to get proceeds from their content. We are committed to fighting any infringements of rights or any other illegal activity under our Service.
Bookmate supports holders of copyright not only by promoting the content and paying proceeds from it, but also by preventing infringement of copyrights.
Every book uploaded by authors and publishers at Bookmate will be automatically compared with already uploaded files. If the rights for the book have been already registered, the book will not be published again.
Thus, it is crucial for us to receive full details of rights holders to prevent infringement of copyright.
Our mission is to provide legal services:
to holders of copyright, that is to promote digital books and audiobooks and collect and share proceeds from their distribution;
to readers, that is to provide them with the best in class applications for reading, listening and accessing a rich collection of the Books.
We continuously work to improve our technologies, so we shall keep providing rights holders with new opportunities to develop publishing and distribution of digital books and audiobooks.
It is Bookmate’s policy to fully comply with the Digital Millennium Copyright Act and all other current copyright protecting laws. We shall immediately remove illegal content upon receiving a relevant takedown notification. We respect the rights of the rights holders and publishers and focus on developing lawful services to receive proceeds from the content at Bookmate Publisher
publisher.bookmate.com
.
If you believe that your copyright has been infringed, please let us know by sending a notification to
copyright@bookmate.com
, including the following:
Identification of the copyrighted work claimed to have been infringed, or, if multiple copyrighted works are concerned, a full list of such illegally used copyrighted works (where possible, please specify the ISBN, the year of publishing, rights for translation of the content, where different from the source language).
Identification of the file that is claimed to be infringing the copyright or to be the subject of infringing activity that is to be removed or access to which is to be disabled: the Bookmate URL.
Information reasonably sufficient to permit the service provider to contact the complaining party, such as an address, telephone number, and an electronic mail address at which the complaining party may be contacted
A statement that the complaining party has a good faith belief that use of the material in the manner complained of is not authorized by the copyright owner, its agent, or the law.
A statement that the information in the notification is accurate, and under penalty of perjury, that the complaining party is authorized to act on behalf of the owner of an exclusive right that is allegedly infringed.
A physical or electronic signature of a person authorized to act on behalf of the owner of an exclusive right that is allegedly infringed.
For your convenience there is a template of notification that you can fill out and send us:
Attention Bookmate:
This communication serves as a statement that:
I am
[the exclusive rights holder | the duly authorized representative of the exclusive rights holder]
for
[title of copyrighted material being infringed upon, and, if possible, additional identifying information such as ISBNs, publication dates, etc. — or, if the material is a web page, the URL]
;
These exclusive rights are being violated by material available upon your site at the following URL(s):
[URLs of infringing material]
;
I have a good faith belief that the use of this material in such a fashion is not authorized by the copyright holder, the copyright holder's agent, or the law;
I state that the information contained in this notification is accurate, and that I am authorized to act on the behalf of the exclusive rights holder for the material in question;
I may be contacted by the following methods:
[postal address, telephone number, and email address]
;
I hereby request that you remove or disable access to this material as it appears on your service in a relevant manner.
Thank you.
Regards,
[your full name or name of the company ]
To make sure that such action is necessary, please consult your legal counsel.
Bookmate shall comply with the copyright acts and we always promptly remove the illegal content, upon receipt of the corresponding notice. In case you consider that the work placed by you on the Bookmate has been removed by mistake, you may file a counter-notice which should contain the following:
User’s name, address, phone number, physical and electronic signature;
Name of the work, name of the author and other identification details of the work and its location on the Bookmate before it is removed or blocked (URL in Bookmate);
Statement under the penalty of perjury, that you have a bona fide belief that the work has been removed or blocked by mistake or due to false identification.
In case of counter-notice filled in in accordance with the requirements stated hereinabove, the Bookmate shall promptly resend your counter-notice to the person, who demanded to remove the work.
In case no suit has been filed against you by the person who sent the notice on copyright infringement within 14 days from the date of receipt of a copy of such counter-notice, then Bookmate shall recover the work, otherwise the work shall be subject to recovery prior to resolution of dispute between the Parties.
